Part (c)

The inflation appears at around 6 so he intrinsic dimensionality is 6-1 therefore the value would be at 5 according to the inflection point criterion.

Part (d)

There are 5 eigenvalues more than 1 so the intrinsic dimensionality is 5 according to Kairsers criterion.

Part (e)

There are 8 eigenvalues values above 0.7 so the intrinsic dimensionality is 8 according to Jollifes criterion.

Part (f)

The intrinsic dimensionality according to inflection point criterion and Kairsers criterion is the same i.e.5 but is different for Jollifes criterion i.e.8.

Part (d)

The answers above does not support the original theoretical framework of this article, because based of the visual graph we can we 2 clusters. Although looking into the kaiser and Jolliffe cluster we can see that for the kaiser we need to keep 3 eigen values. However for the Jolliffe cluster we need to keep 5 eigen values. Therefore both the visual representation and the cluster values does not match with the hypothesize, because for the hypothesize it says that there is only 2 clusters which from 1 through 4 and 5 through 10. Looking at the graph we can see that the first cluster that is 1 through 4 we can see that there is 8 in it, hence it does not support it.
